8 PROPOSED SUBCOMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
9 An Act relating to child care facilities; providing
legislative finding; directing that licensed child
10 care facilities maintain certain staff-to-child
ratios; directing the Department of Human Services to
11 promulgate rules; providing for codification; and
providing an effective date.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 405.6 of Title 10, unless there
17 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. The Oklahoma Legislature finds that maintaining safe,
19 developmentally appropriate child-to-staff ratios is essential for
20 protecting the welfare of children in licensed child care centers
21 while promoting accessibility and affordability for Oklahoma
22 families.
23 B. Licensed child care centers shall maintain the following
24 minimum staff-to-child ratios:
Req. No. 15941 Page 1

1 1. For children from birth through eleven (11) months of age,
2 there shall be one staff member for every five children;
3 2. For children from twelve (12) months of age through twenty-
4 three (23) months of age, there shall be one staff member for every
5 seven children;
6 3. For children from two (2) years of age up to three (3) years
7 of age, there shall be one staff member for every nine children;
8 4. For children from three (3) years of age up to four (4)
9 years of age, there shall be one staff member for every twelve
10 children;
11 5. For children from four (4) years of age through five (5)
12 years of age, there shall be one staff member for every fifteen
13 children; and
14 6. For children six (6) years of age or older, there shall be
15 one staff member for every twenty children.
16 C. The Department of Human Services shall promulgate any rules
17 necessary to bring the Oklahoma Administrative Code into conformity
18 with this act.
19 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
